    "title": "Principal Fleet Manager at Allcargo Logistics International Enterprises",
    "description": "Allcargo Logistics International Enterprises, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Fleet Manager for our Mysuru operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout Allcargo Logistics International Enterprises:\nAllcargo Logistics International Enterprises is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Oversee end-to-end logistics operations for timely delivery\n• Manage a fleet of vehicles and coordinate with drivers\n• Ensure compliance with transportation regulations and safety standards\n• Conduct periodic vendor audits and evaluate logistics partners\n• Optimize delivery routes to reduce cost and improve efficiency\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Manage reverse logistics and return merchandise authorization\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Fleet Management\n• Proficiency in Freight Forwarding\n• Proficiency in WMS\n• Proficiency in INCOTERMS\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in SAP SCM\n• Proficiency in Data Analytics\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Allcargo Logistics International Enterprises!",
